# Environment Variables for Entropy AI Lab Newsletter

## SMTP Configuration for Outlook.com/Hotmail
# These variables are required for sending confirmation emails

# SMTP Server Host (for Outlook.com/Hotmail)
SMTP_HOST=smtp-mail.outlook.com

# SMTP Port (587 for STARTTLS - Outlook.com standard)
SMTP_PORT=587

# Email address to send from (your Outlook.com/Hotmail address)
# Example: yourname@outlook.com or yourname@hotmail.com
SMTP_USER=your-email@outlook.com

# Email password or App Password
# For Outlook.com with 2FA: Create App Password at https://account.microsoft.com/security
# For regular accounts: Use your email password
# Note: If using 2FA (recommended), you MUST use an App Password
SMTP_PASSWORD=your-app-password-here

## Alternative: Resend API (Recommended for Production)
# Sign up at https://resend.com (Free: 3,000 emails/month)
# RESEND_API_KEY=re_your_api_key_here

## Alternative: Web3Forms (Free Forever)
# Sign up at https://web3forms.com
# WEB3FORMS_ACCESS_KEY=your_access_key_here

## Vercel Setup Instructions:
## 1. Go to your Vercel project dashboard
## 2. Navigate to Settings > Environment Variables
## 3. Add each variable above with the corresponding value
## 4. Make sure to add them for Production, Preview, and Development environments
## 5. Redeploy your project after adding environment variables

## Security Notes:
## - NEVER commit this file with real credentials
## - Use strong, unique passwords
## - For Gmail, enable 2FA and use App Passwords
## - For custom domains, ensure SMTP is properly configured
